# Allow injection of Gson or JsonParser (or both) when constructing JsonHubProtocol

This PR allows the user to inject a `Gson` or `JsonParser` (or both) instance when constructing a `JsonHubProtocol`.

## Why
It is currently not possible (or at least very difficult) to transfer model objects with fields of non-primitive types over SignalR, such as `LocalDateTime`. Allowing the user to add more parsing options to the `Gson` instance before constructing the `JsonHubProtocol` solves this issue.

## Compatibility 
This change is non-breaking and modifies very few lines of code. This change adds additional constructors to `JsonHubProtocol`, and keeps the default constructor to ensure that there are no behavior changes for all existing usages of the class.

## Changes
### Before
```java
public JsonHubProtocol() {
    this.gson = new Gson();
    this.jsonParser = new JsonParser();
}
```
### After
```java
public JsonHubProtocol() {
    this(new Gson(), new JsonParser());
}

public JsonHubProtocol(Gson gson) {
    this(gson, new JsonParser());
}

public JsonHubProtocol(JsonParser jsonParser) {
    this(new Gson(), jsonParser);
}

public JsonHubProtocol(Gson gson, JsonParser jsonParser) {
    this.gson = gson;
    this.jsonParser = jsonParser;
}
```

## References
Addresses https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/17519

Related to https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/pull/17774

